org.forgerock.openidm.managed

Interface ManagedObjectSetService


  • public interface ManagedObjectSetService
    An interface for performing actions on a set of managed objects.

    • Method Detail

      • update

        org.forgerock.json.resource.ResourceResponse update(org.forgerock.services.context.Context context,
                                                    org.forgerock.json.resource.Request request,
                                                    String resourceId,
                                                    String rev,
                                                    org.forgerock.json.JsonValue oldValue,
                                                    org.forgerock.json.JsonValue newValue,
                                                    Set<org.forgerock.json.JsonPointer> relationshipFields,
                                                    Set<org.forgerock.json.JsonPointer> alreadyPersistedRelationshipFields)
                                             throws org.forgerock.json.resource.ResourceException
        Performs and update on a managed object. The update will include executing onUpdate and postUpdate scripts as well as performing a sync operation on the managed object.
        Parameters:
        context - the current Context
        request - the source Request
        resourceId - the resource id of the object being modified
        rev - the revision of the object being modified
        oldValue - the old value of the object
        newValue - the new value of the object
        relationshipFields - a set of relationship fields.
        alreadyPersistedRelationshipFields - the set of relationship fields already persisted by the caller. Non-empty set specified only when method invoked by RelationshipProvider when consumed as a relationship endpoint, as it persists the relationship prior to calling this method.
        Returns:
        a ResourceResponse object representing the updated resource
        Throws:
        org.forgerock.json.resource.ResourceException
